data.enText: to be very good at doing sth

data.chText: 她的外语从来都是出类拔萃。
data.enText: She has always excelled in foreign languages.

data.chText: 这个队善于打防守反击。
data.enText: The team excels at turning defence into attack.

data.chText: 他小时候擅长音乐和美术。
data.enText: As a child he excelled at music and art.
to do extremely well and even better than you usually do

data.chText: 里克的烹饪技术一直不错，但这次简直是好上加好。
data.enText: Rick's cooking was always good but this time he really excelled himself.

ex.enText: Tom was exceeding the speed limit.

ex.chText: 工作时间每天不得超过8小时。
ex.enText: Working hours must not exceed 8 hours a day.

synonyms.bx: 指超越职权范围、法律规定等，或超出数量、程度、大小等。

ex.chText: 她在舞蹈方面出类拔萃。

synonyms.bx: 通常指在成就、学识等方面胜过他人，不用进行时。

ex.chText: 中国将在经济上超过日本。
ex.enText: China will surpass Japan in economy.

synonyms.bx: 指在技能、成就等方面超越同类。

value.def: If someone excels in something or excels at it, they are very good at doing it.

example.ex: Caine has always been an actor who excels in irony...
example.tran: 凯恩向来是个擅长讽刺的演员。

example.ex: Mary was a better rider than either of them and she excelled at outdoor sports...
example.tran: 玛丽的骑术比他们俩都要好，而且她擅长户外运动。
他开始在学术上超越他人。

example.ex: I think Krishnan excelled himself in all departments of his game.
example.tran: 我认为克里舍南在比赛的各个环节都有超常的发挥。
